). First segment (seventh trunk segment) smooth, without ornamentation; approximately half width of tergite 6 (

). Second segment (abdomen) dorsally smooth. Furcal rami each with one terminal seta, longer than wide (

), length subequal to length of terminal urosome segment (two outer lateral setae not visible in light micrographs).

